   Coll Engn, Dept Comp Sci \& Engn; IEEE Bangalore Sect},
Abstract = {Financial institutes like banks spend significant effort in identifying
   credit-worthy consumers for lending. In this paper, we study the
   performance of various classification algorithms applied to a real-life
   data set for consumer lending. Various types of classifiers (logistic
   regression, random forest, neural networks) are evaluated and their
   performance compared. The data set is first pre-processed to select best
   attributes and to remove outliers for classification. The performance is
   assessed using various metrics including the classification accuracy,
   precision, recall and specificity. It is found that logistic regression
   yields very good performance. By varying the cutoff ratio in random
   forest it is possible to trade off precision and recall to filter those
   consumers who are credit worth.},
