   ENGINEERING (CONFLUENCE 2019)},
Year = {2019},
Pages = {606-610},
Note = {9th International Conference on Cloud Computing, Data Science and
   Engineering (CONFLUENCE), Amity Univ, Noida, INDIA, JAN 10-11, 2019},
Organization = {IEEE},
Abstract = {Computer forensics has been developed from investigating small cyber
   attacks to exploring the complicated international cyber cases which
   have a tremendous impact on the organization. Even though organization
   knows the type of attacks but still it won't help them to take
   preventive measures across the attack unless they don't know the
   consequences of the attack or the area where the attack is going to
   affect the most. This paper has examined the various types of attacks
   and motives behind those attacks through a questionnaire which was
   randomly distributed to various participants working for any industry or
   organization. The result was analyzed through weka software to propose
   model which uses the consequences mining algorithm. Consequences Mining
   Algorithm will take the motive of attacks as input and will give its
   hidden and visible consequences as output. The proposed model is the
   combination of computer forensics investigation and data mining. Results
   from the model will help the organization to take proactive measures
   against the consequences of the attack.},
