Title = {Anomaly Detection in Admission or Selection Examinations using Data
   Mining Techniques},
Booktitle = {2020 2ND INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE ON SUSTAINABLE TECHNOLOGIES FOR
   INDUSTRY 4.0 (STI)},
Year = {2020},
Note = {2nd International Conference on Sustainable Technologies for Industry
   4.0 (STI), Dhaka, BANGLADESH, DEC 19-20, 2020},
Abstract = {The paper presents the utilization of data mining techniques to detect
   anomaly or fraud in admission or selection examinations. University
   authority and government often arrange admission examinations to narrow
   down the student admission process and recruit employees. However, in
   developing and underdeveloped countries, convicted people manage to
   supply question papers before examination or provide answers to
   candidates in different ways, including digital miniature contact
   devices. To address this issue, we propose an algorithm that utilizes
   Jenks natural breaks clustering method and FP-tree generation method to
   identify the anomaly or fraud in the exam by evaluating the subject wise
   marks. It is easier to classify using the proposed method due to the
   answer pattern, similar in nature, delivered to their candidates by
   criminals. Therefore, our proposed work helps investigate those
   anomalies with clustering of the evaluation marks and fetch the
   suspicious number pattern. Our experimental results show that the
   average F1 score for identifying suspicious patterns is 0.876, which is
   quite a satisfactory result.},
