Organization = {SRM University Andhra Pradesh},
Abstract = {In recent years, cybersecurity intelligence has emerged as an essential
   tool not only for protecting digital assets but also for safeguarding
   the natural environment. As biodiversity faces unprecedented threats
   from climatic shifts, habitat destruction, and pollution, the
   implementation of cyber intelligence represents a novel frontier in the
   protection of natural ecosystems. This paper explores the synergy
   between cybersecurity and biodiversity protection, focusing on how cyber
   intelligence can aid in combating environmental crimes, monitoring
   endangered species, and enhancing conservation efforts. By integrating
   advanced cybersecurity protocols and intelligence into biodiversity
   management, and implementing key technologies such as drones, IoT
   devices, secure data collection, predictive analytics, and blockchain,
   can fortify conservation efforts. By examining case studies, this
   research highlights the transformative impact of advanced technologies
   on protecting nature and various species, thereby providing insights
   into future directions for integrating these fields to preserve our
   planet's biodiversity.},
