   AROFE; SAS Inst Japan; SPSS Japan Inc; Kankodo; Syst Alpha Inc; GCC Inc;
   Yamato Inc; Daiei Dream Co Ltd},
Abstract = {Investigative profiling is an important activity in computer forensics
   that can narrow the search for one or more computer perpetrators. Data
   mining is a technique that has produced good results in providing
   insight into large volumes of data. This paper describes how the
   association rule data mining technique may be employed to generate
   profiles from log data and the methodology used for the interpretation
   of the resulting rule sets. The process relies on background knowledge
   in the form of concept hierarchies and beliefs, commonly available from,
   or attainable by, the computer forensic investigative team. Results
   obtained with the profiling system has identified irregularities in
   computer logs.},
