   Johannesburg, Acad Comp Sci \& Software Engn},
Abstract = {The rampant absorption of Bitcoin as a cryptographic currency, along
   with rising cybercrime activities, warrants utilization of anomaly
   detection to identify potential fraud. Anomaly detection plays a pivotal
   role in data mining since most outlying points contain crucial
   information for further investigation. In the financial world which the
   Bitcoin network is part of by default, anomaly detection amounts to
   fraud detection. This paper investigates the use of trimmed k-means,
   that is capable of simultaneous clustering of objects and fraud
   detection in a multivariate setup, to detect fraudulent activity in
   Bitcoin transactions. The proposed approach detects more fraudulent
   transactions than similar studies or reports on the same dataset.},
